HEADWORD: Porringer
<hw>Por"rin*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>pottanger</ets>, for <ets>pottager</ets>; cf. F. <ets>potager</ets>
a soup basin. See <er>Porridge</er>.]</ety> <def>A porridge dish; esp.,
a bowl or cup from which children eat or are fed; <as>as, a silver
<ex>porringer</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
